HIV/AIDS: China ta ba da rahoton ƙaruwar cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta sanar da cewa yawan al'ummarta da ke rayuwa da cutar kanjamau da HIV ya karu da kashi 14 cikin 100 a duniya.
Ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya sun ce fiye da mutane 820,000 ne cutar ta shafa a ƙasar.
Kimanin sabbin shari'o'i 40,000 aka ruwaito a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018 kadai.
Mafi yawan sababbin cututtuka ana samunsu ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya nuna canji daga abin da ya faru a dā.
A al'adarsa, HIV yana yaɗuwa da sauri a wasu ɓangarorin ƙasar Sin ta hanyar ƙarin jini da aka yi wa mutum da yake da ƙwayoyin cutar.
Amma adadin mutanen da suke kamuwa da cutar ta HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu, in ji ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin da suke wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
A kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da suke da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin yana ƙaruwa da mutane 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i wata matsala ce mai mahimmanci a cikin LGBT jama'ar kasar Sin.
A shekarar 1997 ne aka haramta luwadi a China, amma har yanzu ana nuna wariya ga LGBT.
Domin ƙa'idodin ƙasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 bisa ɗari na maza da suke jima'i da maza za su yi aure da mata.
Yawancin kamuwa da cuta yana zuwa ne daga rashin kāriyar jima'i a waɗannan dangantaka.
Tun a shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar kanjamau ga kowa a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance wannan matsalar.
